sell researchbased drugs medical devices diagnostics and nutritional products it split off the researchbased pharmaceuticals into abbvie in  in  revenues were  billion abbott has a broad range of branded generic pharmaceuticals medical devices diagnostics and nutrition products the companys invitro diagnostics business performs immunoassays and blood screening its medical tests and diagnostic instrument systems are used worldwide by hospitals laboratories blood banks and physician offices to diagnose and monitor diseases such as hiv hepatitis cancer heart failure and metabolic disorders as well as assess other indicators of health in  the company developed the first hiv bloodscreening test abbott pointofcare manufactures diagnostic products for blood analysis to provide health care professionals diagnostics information at the point of patient care abbott also provides pointofcare cardiac assays to the emergency room contents  history  acquisition history  organization  management structure  management practices  ownership  litigation  humira  depakote  sponsorship  see also  notes and references  external links historyedit dr wallace c abbott in  at the age of  wallace abbott – an  graduate of the university of michigan founded the abbott alkaloidal company at the time he was a practicing physician and owned a drug store his innovation was the use of the active part of a medicinal plant generally an alkaloid morphine quinine strychnine and codeine which he formed into tiny dosimetric granules this approach was successful since it produced more consistent and effective dosages for patients abbotts first international affiliate was in london in  and the company later added an affiliate in montreal canada fact  abbott started operations in pakistan as a marketing affiliate in  the company has steadily expanded to comprise a work force of over  employees currently two manufacturing facilities located at landhi and korangi in karachi continue to produce pharmaceutical pr