 wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search for other uses see abbott abbott laboratories type public traded as nyse abt sp  component sp  component industry health care founded   years ago  as abbott alkaloidal company founder dr wallace calvin abbott headquarters lake bluff illinois united states area served worldwide key people miles d white chairman and ceo products branded generic drugs medical devices diagnostic assays nutritional products revenue us billion  operating income us billion  net income us billion  total assets us billion  total equity us billion  number of employees   website wwwabbottcom abbott laboratories is an american worldwide health care company it has  employees and operates in more than  countries the company headquarters are in lake bluff illinois the company was founded by chicago physician wallace calvin abbott in  to formulate known drugs it eventually grew to also sell researchbased drugs medical devices diagnostics and nutritional products it split off the researchbased pharmaceuticals into abbvie in  in  revenues were  billion abbott has a broad range of branded generic pharmaceuticals medical devices diagnostics and nutrition products the companys invitro diagnostics business performs immunoassays and blood screening its medical tests and diagnostic instrument systems are used worldwide by hospitals laboratories blood banks and physician offices to diagnose and monitor diseases such as hiv hepatitis cancer heart failure and metabolic disorders as well as assess other indicators of health in  the company developed the first hiv bloodscreening test abbott pointofcare manufactures diagnostic products for blood analysis to provide health care professionals diagnostics information at the point of patient care abbott also provides pointofcare cardiac assays to the emergency room contents  history  acquisition history  organization  management structure  management practices  ownership  litigation  humira  depakote  sponsorship  see also  notes and references  external links historyedit dr wallace c abbott in  at the age of  wallace abbott – an  graduate of the university of michigan founded the abbott alkaloidal company at the time he was a practicing physician and owned a drug store his innovation was the use of the active part of a medicinal plant generally an alkaloid morphine quinine strychnine and codeine which he formed into tiny dosimetric granules this approach was successful since it produced more consistent and effective dosages for patients abbotts first international affiliate was in london in  and the company later added an affiliate in montreal canada fact  abbott started operations in pakistan as a marketing affiliate in  the company has steadily expanded to comprise a work force of over  employees currently two manufacturing facilities located at landhi and korangi in karachi continue to produce pharmaceutical products expansion continued in  when abbott entered into a joint venture with dainippon pharmaceutical co ltd of osaka japan to manufacture radiopharmaceuticals in  it acquired ross laboratories making ross a wholly owned subsidiary of abbott in  abbotts expansion in europe continued with offices in italy and france abbott laboratories has been present in india for over  years through its subsidiary abbott india limited and it is currently indias largest healthcare products company according to harvard professor lester grinspoon and peter hedblom in  abbott laboratories sold the equivalent of two million doses of methamphetamine in powder form to a long island criminal dealer in  the company acquired knoll the pharmaceutical division of basf in  it divested the selsun blue brand to chattem later in  the company sold clear eyes and murine to prestige brandscitation needed in  it spun off its hospital products division into a new  employee company named hospira and acquired therasense a diabetescare company which it merged with its medisense division to become abbott diabetes care in  abbott assisted boston scientific in its purchase of guidant corporation as part of the agreement abbott purchased the vascular device division of guidant in  ross was renamed abbott nutrition in  abbott acquired kos pharmaceuticals for  billion in cashcitation needed at the time of acquisition kos marketed niaspan which raises levels of “good” or hdl cholesterol and advicor a niaspan combination drug for patients with multiple lipid disorders in january  the company agreed to sell its in vitro diagnostics and pointofcare diagnostics divisions to general electric for more than  billion these units were slated to be integrated into the ge healthcare business unit the transaction was approved by the boards of directors of abbott and ge and was targeted to close in the first half of  however on july   abbott announced that it had terminated its agreement with ge because the parties could not agree on the terms of the deal on september   the company completed the sale of the uk manufacturing plant at queenborough to aesica pharmaceuticals a private equityowned uk manufacturer no announcements have been made restricting the movement of staff to abbott unlike other sell outs on february   the company completed its acquisition of advanced medical optics based in santa ana california in  abbott opened a satellite research and development facility at research park university of illinois at urbanachampaigncitation needed in february  abbott completed its  billion eur  billion acquisition of the pharmaceuticals unit of solvay sa this provided abbott with a large and complementary portfolio of pharmaceutical products and also expanding its presence in key emerging markets on march   the company completed its acquisition of a hollywood floridabased lims company starlims under the terms of the deal abbott laboratories acquired the company for  per share in an allcash transaction valued at  million on may   abbott laboratories said it would buy piramal healthcare ltds healthcare solutions unit for  billion to become the biggest drug company in india in october  the company announced that it planned to separate into two companies one researchbased pharmaceuticals and the other in medical devices generic drugs sold internationally and consumer products with device company retaining the abbott name the company announced that the other company would be named abbvie in march  in preparation for the reorganization abbott made severe budget cuts and took a  million charge in q to pay for the restructuring the separation was effective as of january   abbvie was officially listed in the new york stock exchange on january   on may   it was announced that abbott would acquire the holding company kalo pharma internacional sl for  billion in order to secure the  it held of chilean pharmaceutical company cfr pharmaceuticals which the company said would more than double its branded generic drug portfolio in june  the company entered into a definitive agreement to take over russian pharmaceutical manufacturer veropharm voronezh in a deal worth  million abbott which already employs  people in russia said it planned to set up a manufacturing presence in the country when the deal closed in february  the company announced it would acquire alere for  billion in late april of the same year abbott announced it would acquire st jude medical for  billion each share receiving  in cash   shares of abbott common stock equating to an approximate value of  acquisition historyedit the following is an illustration of the companys major mergers and acquisitions and historical predecessors this is not a comprehensive list   illustration of the companys mergers acquisitions spinoffs and historical predecessors abbott laboratories abbott alkaloidal company est  ross laboratories acq  smithkline beecham acq  knoll acq  selsun blue sold to chattem  murine sold to prestige brands clear eyes sold to prestige brands  guidant vascular device div acq  therasense acq  hospira spun off  advanced medical optics acq  intralase corp acq  solvay pharmaceuticals acq  starlims acq  lab data management ltd acq  abbvie spun off  idev technologies acq  optimedica corporation acq  veropharm acq  topera inc acq  kalo pharma internacional sl acq  cfr pharmaceuticals alere incbr acq  epocal inc acq  arriva medical acq  st jude medicalbr acq  st jude medical est  pacesetter inc acq  daig corporation acq  heart valve company acq remaining  from joint venture with hancock jaffe laboratories  biocor industria acq  ventritex acq  tyco international angioseal div acq  endocardial solutions acq  advanced neuromodulation systems acq  mediguide acq  aga medical acq  lightlab imaging acq  cardiomems inc acq  endosense acq  spinal modulation acq  nanostim inc acq  thoratec corporation acq  apica cardiovascular limited acq  levitronix medical div acq  getinge group heart pump technology div acq  thermo cardiosystems acq  organizationedit abbott office abbotts core businesses focus on pharmaceuticals medical devices and nutritional products which have been supplemented through acquisitions as of update the firms divisions are diabetes care glucose monitoring devices diagnostics hematology immunodiagnostic oncology and clinical chemistry including the istat endovascular established pharmaceuticals epd branded generic drugs sold exclusively in developing markets medical devices medical optics nutrition baby nutrition eg similac isomil and gain adult health products eg ensure and zoneperfect and special dietary needs eg glucerna and juven management structureedit miles d white is chairman and ceo he joined abbott in  serving in management positions including senior vice president of diagnostic operations and executive vice president he was elected to the board of directors in april  to chief executive officer in  and to chairman of the board in april citation needed management practicesedit along with being ranked th on the  fortune  list of largest usbased corporationcitation needed abbott was named one of the  top  employers by the journal science and listed as a top  company for women by working mother magazine and the national association for female executivescitation needed the company has also been named one of the worlds most admired companies by fortune magazine every year since  – ranking no  in medical equipment in  and citation needed abbott has also been recognized for  consecutive years for sustainability leadership through its inclusion on the dow jones sustainability index djsicitation needed the top employers institute designated abbott as a great place to work in europe and china in citation needed diversityinc magazine has recognized abbott repeatedly as a top  company for diversity and additionally the dave thomas foundation ranked the company as a best company thanks to its generous adoption benefitscitation needed ownershipedit as of  abbott laboratories shares are mainly held by institutional investors the vanguard group blackrock state street corporation and others litigationedit humiraedit in march  british company cambridge antibody technology cat stated its wish to initiate discussions regarding the applicability of the royalty offset provisions for humira adalimumab with abbott laboratories in the high court of london in december  the judgment ruled for cat abbott was required to pay cat us million some of which was to be passed to its partners in development of this sum the medical research council united kingdom mrc received usm and in addition abbott was asked to pay the mrc a further usm over five years from  providing that humira remains on the marketcitation needed depakoteedit on october   the company was charged with a  million fine and  million forfeiture for illegal marketing and in a plea agreement was assessed the secondlargest criminal fine in us history for a drug company us district court judge samuel g wilson of the western district of virginia imposed it given abbotts guilty plea related to its unlawful promotion of depakote for uses not approved by the fda abbott had advertised depakote to be used to control behavioral disturbances for patients with dementia and schizophrenia without fda approval in addition abbott marketed depakote for other psychiatric conditions in adults including depression anxiety obsessivecompulsive disorder posttraumatic stress disorder alcohol and drug withdrawal and psychiatric conditions in children including conduct disorders attention deficit disorder and autism the court also ordered abbott to a fiveyear term of probation and court supervision shareholders then brought derivative suits against the company directors for breach of fiduciary duty the parties reached a negotiated settlement in which abbott agreed to beef up its internal controls and paid the plaintiffs attorney fees sponsorshipedit since  abbott is the title sponsor of the world marathon majors see alsoedit list of biotechnology companies list of illinois companies list of pharmaceutical companies notes and referencesedit  a b c d e f  abbott annual report k   contacts  abbott us    abbott annual report k   abbott laboratories archived  july  at the wayback machine abbott laboratories retrieved july    abbott laboratories company history funding universe retrieved april     about us   its essential to be part of the extraordinary future india is building miles d white intodayin   grinspoon lester hedblom peter  the speed culture amphetamine use and abuse in america cambridge massachusetts harvard university press p  isbn  oclc    layne rachel lopatto elizabeth july   ge abbott end  billion diagnostic sale deal update bloomberg news   abbott press release february   abbott completes acquisition of solvay pharmaceuticals archived from the original on  march  retrieved march     abbott laboratories feb  current report form k filing date feb   pdf secdatabasecom retrieved dec     abbott press release march   abbott completes acquisition of