n at the point of patient care abbott also provides pointofcare cardiac assays to the emergency room contents  history  acquisition history  organization  management structure  management practices  ownership  litigation  humira  depakote  sponsorship  see also  notes and references  external links historyedit dr wallace c abbott in  at the age of  wallace abbott – an  graduate of the university of michigan founded the abbott alkaloidal company at the time he was a practicing physician and owned a drug store his innovation was the use of the active part of a medicinal plant generally an alkaloid morphine quinine strychnine and codeine which he formed into tiny dosimetric granules this approach was successful since it produced more consistent and effective dosages for patients abbotts first international affiliate was in london in  and the company later added an affiliate in montreal canada fact  abbott started operations in pakistan as a marketing affiliate in  the company has steadily expanded to comprise a work force of over  employees currently two manufacturing facilities located at landhi and korangi in karachi continue to produce pharmaceutical products expansion continued in  when abbott entered into a joint venture with dainippon pharmaceutical co ltd of osaka japan to manufacture radiopharmaceuticals in  it acquired ross laboratories making ross a wholly owned subsidiary of abbott in  abbotts expansion in europe continued with offices in italy and france abbott laboratories has been present in india for over  years through its subsidiary abbott india limited and it is currently indias largest healthcare products company according to harvard professor lester grinspoon and peter hedblom in  abbott laboratories sold the equivalent of two million doses of methamphetamine in powder form to a long island criminal dealer in  the company acquired knoll the pharmaceutical division of basf in  it divested the selsun blue brand to chattem later in  the company sold clear eyes and murine to prestige brandscitation needed in  it spun off its hospital products division into a new  employee company named hospira and acquired therasense a diabetescare company which it merged with its medisense division to become abbott diabetes care in  abbott assisted boston scientific in its purchase of guidant corporation as part of the agreement abbott purchased the vascular device division of guidant in  ross was renamed abbott nutrition in  abbott acquired kos pharmaceuticals for  billion in cashcitation needed at the time of acquisition kos marketed niaspan which raises levels of “good” or hdl cholesterol and advicor a niaspan combination drug for patients with multiple lipid disorders in january  the company agreed to sell its in vitro diagnostics and pointofcare diagnostics divisions to general electric for more than  billion these units were slated to be integrated into the ge healthcare business unit the transaction was approved by the boards of directors of abbott and ge and was targeted to close in the first half of  however on july   abbott announced that it had terminated its agreement with ge because the parties could not agree on the terms of the deal on september   the company completed the sale of the uk manufacturing plant at queenborough to aesica pharmaceuticals a private equityowned uk manufacturer no announcements have been made restricting the movement of staff to abbott unlike other sell outs on february   the company completed its acquisition of advanced medical optics based in santa ana california in  abbott opened a satellite research and development facility at research park university of illinois at urbanachampaigncitation needed in february  abbott completed its  billion eur  billion acquisition of the pharmaceuticals unit of solvay sa this provided abbott with a large and complementary portfolio of pharmaceutical products and also expanding its presence in key emerging markets on march   the company completed its acquisition of a hollywood floridabased lims company starlims under the terms of the deal abbott laboratories acquired the company for  per share in an allcash transaction valued at  million on may   abbott laboratories said it would buy piramal healthcare ltds healthcare solutions unit for  billion to become the biggest drug company in india in october  the company announced that it planned to separate into two companies one researchbased pharmaceuticals and the other in medical devices generic drugs sold internationally and consumer products with device company retaining the abbott name the company announced that the other company would be named abbvie in march  in preparation for the reorganization abbott made severe budget cuts and took a  million charge in q to pay for the restructuring the separation was effective as of january   abbvie was officially listed in the new york stock exchange on january   on may   it was announced that abbott would acquire the holding company kalo pharma internacional sl for  billion in order to secure the  it held of chilean pharmaceutical company cfr pharmaceuticals which the company said would more than double its branded generic drug portfolio in june  the company entered into a definitive agreement to take over russian pharmaceutical manufacturer veropharm voronezh in a deal worth  million abbott which already employs  people in russia said it planned to set up a manufacturing presence in the country when the deal closed in february  the company announced it would acquire alere for  billion in late april of the same year abbott announced it would acquire st jude medical for  billion each share receiving  in cash   shares of abbott common stock equating to an approximate value of  acquisition historyedit the following is an illustration of the companys major mergers and acquisitions and historical predecessors this is not a comprehensive list   illustration of the companys mergers acquisitions spinoffs and historical predecessors 